==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stephanite
<hw>Steph"an*ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[So named after
the Archduke <ets>Stephan</ets>, mining director of Austria.]</ety>
<fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A sulphide of antimony and silver of an
iron-black color and metallic luster; called also <altname>black
silver</altname>, and <altname>brittle silver ore</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stephanotis</ent>⟦br⟧
